definitions.definition: A headsail resembling a genoa or a jib but with a high-cut clew , normally used together with a staysail . A sailing boat is typically equipped with three yankee sails of different sizes, number one being the largest.
alternative letter-case form of Yankee from the NATO/ICAO Phonetic Alphabet .
